# Page rules

## Page intent
Each page should have a clear purpose:
- explain an offer
- build trust
- answer obvious customer questions
- create a clear next step

Do not overload pages with unnecessary complexity.

## Preferred priorities
When editing a page, prioritize:
1. clear headline
2. clear service explanation
3. trust signals
4. clear CTA
5. mobile readability
6. fast performance

## Content structure
Prefer this order when appropriate:
- headline
- short supporting statement
- core value or service explanation
- proof or trust section
- CTA

## Guardrails
- Do not add filler sections just to make the page longer
- Do not use vague marketing language when plain language is stronger
- Do not add fake testimonials, fake counts, fake project numbers, or fake urgency
- Do not invent case studies or credentials

## UX expectations
- Make sure pages work well on mobile first
- Avoid oversized blocks of text
- Keep spacing consistent
- Preserve readable contrast
- Make CTA buttons obvious and consistent